msgid "# CPU Binding"
msgstr "# CPU 绑定"

msgid ""
"**Starting from vllm-ascend v0.18.0rc1, CPU binding is enabled by default on\n"
"ARM-based Ascend servers.**"
msgstr "**从 vllm-ascend v0.18.0rc1 开始，CPU 绑定在基于 ARM 的 Ascend 服务器上默认启用。**"

msgid ""
"**You usually do not need to configure it manually.** Set `enable_cpu_binding`\n"
"only when you want to disable it or make the default explicit."
msgstr "**通常您无需手动配置。** 仅当您想禁用它或明确默认行为时，才设置 `enable_cpu_binding`。"

msgid "## Benefits of CPU Binding"
msgstr "## CPU 绑定的优势"

msgid ""
"CPU Binding improves **host-side scheduling** for multi-socket ARM servers with\n"
"Ascend NPUs. It is designed to solve three common host-side inference performance issues:"
msgstr "CPU 绑定改进了搭载 Ascend NPU 的多插槽 ARM 服务器的**主机端调度**。它旨在解决三个常见的主机端推理性能问题："

msgid ""
"- **Lower cross-NUMA traffic.** Worker processes stay closer to the CPU and\n"
"  memory resources selected for their active NPU, reducing remote NUMA access.\n"
"- **Lower context-switch overhead from thread preemption.** Key runtime threads\n"
"  run on stable CPU ranges, reducing scheduler movement and CPU contention on\n"
"  busy hosts.\n"
"- **Better latency stability and multi-worker isolation.** Independent workers\n"
"  avoid sharing the same CPU/NUMA resources, which helps reduce tail-latency\n"
"  jitter and makes throughput more predictable during multi-NPU serving."
msgstr ""
"- **降低跨 NUMA 流量。** 工作进程更靠近为其活跃 NPU 选择的 CPU 和内存资源，从而减少远程 NUMA 访问。\n"
"- **降低线程抢占带来的上下文切换开销。** 关键运行时线程在稳定的 CPU 范围内运行，减少了繁忙主机上的调度器移动和 CPU 争用。\n"
"- **更好的延迟稳定性和多工作进程隔离。** 独立的工作进程避免共享相同的 CPU/NUMA 资源，这有助于减少尾延迟抖动，并使多 NPU 服务期间的吞吐量更可预测。"

msgid ""
"This feature is a host-side performance optimization. **It does not change model\n"
"execution logic or numerical outputs.** When memory migration support is\n"
"unavailable, CPU affinity still works, but memory locality may be worse and\n"
"latency or throughput may degrade."
msgstr ""
"此功能是主机端性能优化。**它不会改变模型执行逻辑或数值输出。** 当内存迁移支持不可用时，CPU "
"亲和性仍然有效，但内存局部性可能会变差，延迟或吞吐量可能会下降。"

